										<P class="MsoNormal">Most of the programs need to store and retrieve data.</P>
										<P class="MsoNormal">Serious, multi user business application can put high demand 
											on underlining database. Business critical applications must not suffer from 
											slow response times. Fortunately, there are database products that can meet all 
											of your needs, the only catch is that you need to do proper database design.</P>
										<P class="MsoNormal">If a database is not normalized, if queries are poorly 
											written, if users are trying to modify data simultaneously… can lead to poor 
											performance, users’ dissatisfaction and lost customers.</P>
										<P class="MsoNormal">We specialize in working with Microsoft SQL Server relational 
											database management system (RDBMS).</P>
										<P class="MsoNormal">We can design database for you. To achieve best response times 
											for your database, we will create entity relational diagrams then:</P>
										<UL>
											<LI>
												<DIV class="MsoNormal">normalize
												</DIV>
											<LI>
												<DIV class="MsoNormal">and if needed&nbsp;purposely denormalize&nbsp;your database.
												</DIV>
											</LI>
										</UL>
										<P class="MsoNormal">We will do calculations for:</P>
										<UL>
											<LI>
												<DIV class="MsoNormal">database sizing and
												</DIV>
											<LI>
												<DIV class="MsoNormal">capacity planning.
												</DIV>
											</LI>
										</UL>
										<P class="MsoNormal">We will tell you what kind of hardware you would need to meet 
											your desired performance, this will include:</P>
										<UL>
											<LI>
												<DIV class="MsoNormal">number of CPUs,
												</DIV>
											<LI>
												<DIV class="MsoNormal">memory,
												</DIV>
											<LI>
												<DIV class="MsoNormal">number and type&nbsp;for hard drives and
												</DIV>
											<LI>
												<DIV class="MsoNormal">what RAID would suite the best your system.</DIV>
											</LI>
										</UL>
										<P class="MsoNormal">We can help you take advantage of:</P>
										<UL>
											<LI>
												<DIV class="MsoNormal">stored procedures,
												</DIV>
											<LI>
												<DIV class="MsoNormal">triggers,
												</DIV>
											<LI>
												<DIV class="MsoNormal">user defined functions to further improve performance and 
													maintain integrity.</DIV>
											</LI>
										</UL>
										<P class="MsoNormal">We can determine what would be the best use of:</P>
										<UL>
											<LI>
												<DIV class="MsoNormal">clustered and
												</DIV>
											<LI>
												<DIV class="MsoNormal">non-clustered indexes based on your queries.
												</DIV>
											</LI>
										</UL>
										<P class="MsoNormal">You might need to take advantage of:</P>
										<UL>
											<LI>
												<DIV class="MsoNormal">indexed views,</DIV>
											<LI>
												<DIV class="MsoNormal">or full text search, features that are not known to many 
													users.</DIV>
											</LI>
										</UL>
										<P class="MsoNormal">If you have a sales force or similar architecture that 
											requires disconnected users, we will set up replication model that best suits 
											your needs, so when these disconnected users are back on-line data will be 
											replicated and synchronized.</P>
										<P class="MsoNormal">We can help you take advantage of security to protect not only 
